hey i'm working on this embedded c++ project for an automotive sensor module and we're hitting a wall. the system runs fine for about 4 hours then the ram just slowly exhausts until it crashes. i think there's a leak somewhere in our buffer management. 

can u look at this snippet and tell me how i should go about systematically finding where the memory is dropping?

```cpp
void process_sensor_data(uint8_t* raw_input, size_t len) {
    // Allocate buffer for telemetry packet
    TelemetryPacket* packet = new TelemetryPacket();

    if (packet->initialize(raw_input, len)) {
        log_telemetry(packet);
    } else {
        // potential error path
        return; 
    }

    // if certain conditions met, we buffer for retry
    if (get_network_status() == STATUS_RETRY) {
        retry_queue.push_back(packet);
    } else {
        delete packet;
    }
}
```

